zh:
{'title': 'k0s: Yet Another Lightweight Kubernetes Distribution?', 'description': '隨著 Kubernetes 主宰容器編排領域，其複雜性和資源需求促使人們尋求更輕便的替代方案。本次講座將探討 k0s，這是一個符合 CNCF 標準的 Kubernetes 發行版，以其輕量級和易於維護的設計而受到讚譽。我們將檢視 k0s 的架構，強調其最小依賴性和簡化的管理特點，包括單一 binary 的安裝模式等。

通過將 k0s 與其他發行版如 k3s 和 minikube 進行比較，我們將突顯其在從裸機到雲端各種部署場景中的優勢。我們將展示 k0s 為何提供了一種更簡單卻功能完整的 Kubernetes 採用方法。

此外，我們將簡要介紹 k0smotron，它能夠在集群內創建一個 Kubernetes 控制平面，便於實現 Kubernetes 作為一項服務。這一功能強調了 k0s 在多樣化環境中增強可擴展性和管理能力的能力。'}

en:
{'title': 'k0s: Yet Another Lightweight Kubernetes Distribution?', 'description': "As Kubernetes dominates container orchestration, its complexity and resource demands drive interest in lighter alternatives. This talk explores k0s, a CNCF-compliant Kubernetes distribution celebrated for its lightweight, easy-to-maintain design. We will examine k0s's architecture, emphasizing its minimal dependencies and simplified management, which includes a single-binary setup process.

Comparing k0s to other distributions like k3s and minikube, we highlight its advantages across various deployment scenarios, from bare-metal to the cloud. We'll demonstrate why k0s offers a simpler, yet functional approach to Kubernetes adoption.

Additionally, we introduce k0smotron, which enables the creation of a Kubernetes control plane within a cluster, facilitating Kubernetes as a Service. This feature underscores k0s's capability to enhance scalability and management in diverse environments."}

{'title': 'OONI Partner Gathering 2024 and Promoting OONI Strategies with Local Communities', 'description': 'After joining the Open Culture Foundation (OCF) in 2023, we discovered OONI amidst a backlog of dormant projects. We decided to initiate the analysis of OONI observation data and began regularly publishing Taiwan Observation Reports. As one of the global promotional community partners of OONI, the significance of promoting the OONI network observation tool locally became evident. By analyzing observation data, we were able to adjust our local promotion strategies.

In May 2024, we participated in the first in-person OONI Partner Gathering, which invited about 40 partners from 30 countries. During this event, we collaboratively discussed the state of internet censorship in different regions, exchanged insights on tool usage and research findings, and shared experiences concerning how to update and refine testing lists.

We aim to share our strategies on participating in international projects, the type of support local teams can offer, and ways to share local achievements with the project team members. Additionally, we will discuss how to engage local community partners in participating in international projects. This session will be presented from the perspective of the Open Culture Foundation, discussing the reactivation of the project, our aspirations to establish a data analysis team in Taiwan, and our potential role in supporting other regional partners with observation data.'}

{'title': 'Bringing the Taiwan Open Source Community to FOSDEM', 'description': 'FOSDEM is an annual conference for developers of free and open-source software held at the Université Libre de Bruxelles in Belgium. Every year, it attracts developers from around the world to share their knowledge and presentations. Starting in 2023, the Open Culture Foundation and COSCUP began setting up a booth at FOSDEM to promote Taiwan's open source community and projects. Through the foundation’s project "International Conference Support Program - Taking You to the World with Open Source," they led two participants, who successfully passed the selection process, to FOSDEM.

This session will cover how we planned our booth activities before departure, how we gathered information about the Taiwanese open-source community and invited participation, how we created or planned to showcase the achievements and characteristics of Taiwan’s open-source community. It will also provide an overview of the "International Conference Support Program - Taking You to the World with Open Source" project execution and application process. Finally, we will discuss future plans and how to increase the international visibility and participation of Taiwan's open source community.

The session primarily shares experiences from the preparation to participation in FOSDEM 2024, the situations encountered while liaising with the Taiwanese open-source community, and how to share our achievements in an international setting, among other topics.'}

zh:
{'title': 'RadioBrowser API - 由社群維護的線上廣播及電視資料庫', 'description': "Regarding online video streaming, it is easy to find YouTube or Twitch. But what about radio broadcasting online? 

We are going to introduce RadioBrowser.API. This community-driven open-source project provides structural, machine-friendly data for application developers to easily find a radio station worldwide.

Unlike video streaming, where platforms like YouTube and Twitch dominate, finding service providers for online radio broadcasting can be daunting. Online radio content providers typically operate on their own servers embedded in their websites. This setup often leads to a cumbersome user experience, with multiple clicks required to change a radio station, and the ' tune-in' experience can feel like a thing of the past. However, with Radio-Browser.API,  finding a radio station is as simple as a single click, offering a welcome relief from the usual complexities."}

en:
{'title': 'RadioBrowser API - A community driven database focus on internet radio and TV stations', 'description': 'When it comes to online video streaming, it is pretty easy to come up with YouTube or Twitch. But what about radio broadcasting online? 

We are going to introduce RadioBrowser.API. It's a community-driven open-source project, providing structural, machine-friendly data for application developers to easily find a radio station all over the world.

Unlike video streaming, it is difficult to find an unicorn PaaS service provider for online radio broadcasting. Nowadays, online radio content provider usually plays on their own server, embedded in their own websites. It takes multiple clicks to change a radio station, and the "Tune-in" user experience no longer exists. However, by integrating Radio-Browser.API in your media player,  finding a radio station is just a click.'}

zh:
{'title': 'Optimizing High-Frequency Trading Systems with Userspace RCU', 'description': 'This proposal explores the innovative application of the open-source Read-Copy-Update (RCU) mechanism to optimize high-frequency trading systems. RCU is a powerful synchronization technique that enables rapid data access, which is crucial in trading environments where milliseconds can make the difference between success and failure.

We will introduce the different flavors of Userspace RCU and delve into the specific implementation details of the RCU variant we used in a real-world case study. By sharing this practical example, we will demonstrate techniques for integrating Userspace RCU to significantly improve real-time data handling and system responsiveness in high-frequency trading applications. Attendees will learn how to select the most appropriate RCU flavor and effectively incorporate it to address the unique challenges of these low-latency systems.

The overarching goal is to showcase how leveraging RCU can boost the performance of high-frequency trading, while also encouraging innovative approaches to tackle the technical obstacles inherent in this domain.'}

