{'title': 'Building a Hospital Digital Transformation Ecosystem with Rails (Ruby on Rails) and Docker Open Source Technologies', 'description': 'Building upon the rapid development capabilities of Rails (Ruby on Rails) for Proof of Concept (PoC) projects, leveraging open-source technology stacks for cost-effectiveness, and minimizing time to market, we aim to quickly deploy user stories to directly engage with users, validate outcomes against user expectations, and continuously iterate and adjust based on user feedback. This iterative process allows for the emergence of new requirements, better ideas, and creativity, rapidly iterating towards a system truly tailored to user needs.

This approach gradually dismantles traditional client-server hospital information systems, breaking down existing system silos and fostering a Minimum Viable Product (MVP) mindset, establishing multiple small victories to facilitate comprehensive digital transformation in hospitals.

Furthermore, leveraging open-source Docker and promoting a healthcare DevOps culture, we implement CI/CD pipelines for automated deployment, effectively utilizing existing resources while reducing development and maintenance costs. Hospital digital transformation should encompass clinical information systems (outpatient, emergency, inpatient, surgery), medical imaging, electronic medical records, peripheral system integration, pharmaceutical and medical supplies inventory, administrative support, healthcare financing, accounting, human resources, and even Environmental, Social, and Governance (ESG) aspects. All of these require system development and integration, and we aim to establish a comprehensive healthcare information system ecosystem through innovation and openness in open-source technology.'}

zh:
{'title': '對談：開源桌遊的挑戰 - 遊戲結束後，開放還會在嗎？', 'description': '以「開源星手村」這款桌遊的緣起開頭，先介紹什麼是開源、從開源精神衍伸而出的開放資料與開放政府分別是什麼概念，又為我們的生活帶來什麼影響。透過概念搭配實際案例的講解，讓參與者了解開源所代表的「開放文化」，蘊含著共享資源、跨領域協作等意義。

與談夥伴們將在這場議程中，將談談過往的帶桌遊的經驗、同時分享 OCF 2024 年嘗試轉成團康模式入校配合推廣開源經驗；同時邀請專業桌遊團隊「桌弄 DrawNow」分享其將桌遊轉換成「大班制的團康玩法」進入校園的議題推廣經驗；另外長期貢獻本專案的工程師 Ben，也將分享將星手村桌遊轉換到「線上」的嘗試與困境。

在論壇中，也邀請過去曾經玩過桌遊的朋友們，如果桌遊要帶到他們本身的場域時可以有哪些變化的玩法。在這場論壇中，期待各來自開源社群的朋友們，可以再論壇中尋找到可以將桌遊借回去、應用並開放經驗成果的可能性。建立開發桌遊的志工、使用者們，可一同討論桌遊未來發展與志工一同持續協作貢獻的可能性。'}

