{'title': 'Establishing the Taiwan FHIR Open Registry Platform', 'description': 'The FHIR Implementation Guide Registry is a central repository dedicated to collecting and managing FHIR Implementation Guides. These guides are compiled by various government agencies, private organizations, healthcare institutions, and communities, providing standardized guidelines for the implementation of FHIR standards across different systems and environments.

Currently, international IG Registries are already in place. Following the adoption of FHIR standards in Taiwan, the government launched the TW Core Implementation Guide (IG) Management Platform in 2022 under the Ministry of Health and Welfare’s Electronic Medical Records Promotion Zone. However, the review mechanism of this Registry is relatively stringent. As FHIR continues to be promoted in Taiwan, more organizations are developing IGs and attempting cross-institutional exchanges. Due to these reasons, we have established the TW Open Registry platform, providing an accessible platform for locating IGs and achieving the goal of promoting healthcare information interoperability.

This session will introduce the structure, composition, community operation mechanisms, and processes of the Taiwan FHIR Open Registry, and compare it with the government Registry. It will demonstrate how developers can quickly obtain the desired Implementation Guides through the IG Registry. Additionally, by integrating with MI-TW interoperability events, the Taiwan FHIR Open Registry will achieve more in-depth practical applications.'}

